    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nPressing `:` while the message window is open displays `f/d/j: screen/page/line down, b/u/k: up, <Esc>: stop paging` above the output. Additionally, typing `f`, `d`, `j`, `b`, `u`, `k`, or `<Esc>` in this state behaves weirdly.\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/347f47ee-9567-4f08-ac52-9efa4961812d\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean`\n- `:lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable {}`\n- `:hi`\n- `:`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt doesn't do that.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2700+g6dfcb2b784",
