            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> This is not a glitched UI1 pager but the dialog window (which supports paging).\n\nGotcha. I've updated the title.\n\n> What's weird about the behavior?\n\nIt gets in the way of typing a command. Any command that contains the letters `f`, `d`, or `j` gets messed up. For example, try running `:hi` and `:bd` in succession: you cannot type the `d` in `:bd`. When I type `:` I want to enter a command, not page output; especially when the `g<` pager is not open.\n\nAdditionally, when themed, `f/d/j: screen/page/line down, b/u/k: up, <Esc>: stop paging` looks really ugly (using [catppuccin-macchiato](https://github.com/catppuccin/nvim)):\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ae4abcd2-7673-4e09-a8fb-ebe1d0c2d41b\" />",
